President Muhammadu Buhari, on Friday, sent messages of congratulations to two chieftains of the All Progressives Congress (APC) Rotimi Amaechi, the Minister of Transportation, and a reputable businessman, Alhaji Nasiru Haladu Danu, on the conferment of chieftaincy titles on them tomorrow, Saturday by the Daura Emirate Council. Buhari said the conferment of the title of “Dan Amana,” (the trusted one) to Amaechi is a clear commitment to the melodious relationship between the nation’s diverse cultures. Danu is being turbaned as Tafida Babba of Daura. This was disclosed in a statement by the Senior Special Assistant (Media and Publicity), Garba Shehu. The President commended Ameachi “for working with enormous energy to make the CHANGE we promised Nigerians a reality,” noting that “the change we are witnessing in the transport sector is an extraordinary legacy.” Buhari will not be at the event on Saturday but has designated a delegation of three, made up of the Ministers of Aviation, Senator Hadi Sirika, Water Resources, Eng Sulaiman Adamu, and Shehu to represent him.